  "created_at_utc": "2026-06-15T01:43:47.697358+00:00",
  "skill_name": "ultracode",
  "activation": "$ultracode only",
  "notes": "PACKAGE_MANIFEST.json excludes itself from the file hash list. v3.6.0: change-scoped, provenance-aware adversarial gate (adversarially reviewed) so read-only audits stop failing on pre-existing code while genuinely dangerous added changes still fail.",
  "primary_changes": [
    "Adversarial gate is CHANGE-SCOPED and provenance-aware (uc_adversarial_verify.py): git-available+empty-diff -> scope=empty-clean (no whole-repo scan); the root-cause fix for read-only audits failing on pre-existing code.",
    "Diff mode scans ONLY added lines (parse_added_lines over git diff --unified=0, unioned with --cached) via contiguous-block matching so multi-line forms (two-line except/pass) still match; new/untracked files are unioned into scope and scanned whole; non-ASCII paths handled via core.quotepath=false.",
    "Only diff findings on a non-read-only run can hard-fail. Explicit --path, no-git fallback, and any read-only run (uc_adversarial_verify --read-only or run.json read_only) are advisory: warn, never block. gate_status separates gating vs advisory and exposes completion_allowed.",
    "dangerous-delete is now target-aware (_dangerous_delete mirrors the safety hook): rm -rf on a real root/home/glob/single-segment-absolute target, GNU long flags, shutil.rmtree literal root/home, and disk-wipe (mkfs/dd/>/dev) — NOT routine cleanup like rm -rf dist/. test-disabled adds unittest.skip/skipTest/xit/xdescribe/t.Skip; placeholder catches raise NotImplemented; generated/minified files skipped by average-line-length.",
    "uc_verify.py --read-only and no-change runs suppress 'verification-detected-not-executed'.",
    "uc_route.py adds a read_only capability flag; uc_bootstrap.py writes read_only into run.json and emits read-only-aware plan phases.",
    "Stop hook (uc_hook_router.py) trusts gate.completion_allowed and run.json read_only, and only releases a read-only run when verification.json has no failures."
  ],
